
[1]steddily

   STEADILY, STEDDILY, adv.

   1. With firmness of standing or position; without tottering, shaking or
   leaning. He kept his arm steddily directed to the object.

   2. Without wavering, inconstancy or irregularity; without deviating. He
   steddily pursues his studies.
